We miss you and are so excited to welcome you back to school this fall! We are planning for a school year of learning together in an in-person classroom environment. However, we realize things can change between now and the first day of school. Take a moment to watch this video to hear more about how we’re preparing for the 2020-21 school year. We created detailed plans around four learning scenarios. These plans are in-line with our state's department of education plan, which outlines required and recommended safety protocols for the 2020-21 school year based on the status of coronavirus in our community.
For the most up to date information on back to school plan, please visit: https://www.nhaschools.com/en/COVID-19

With so much going on around us today. It is tricky to figure out what's true or not. Let's take a moment and learn how to get better at interpreting what NEWS we see on the internet. Watch the video. Printing is optional, complete the grade-appropriate Digital Media Sheet. Students, explore your favorite game site on the Internet for 20 min. Most importantly, be safe and have fun!

post_text:
Hi Scholars!

Let's review the power of KIND. The Internet is a powerful tool that can be used to be kind or unkind to others. We come across all kinds of content online and on social media. Some of what we see is rude, mean, or even hurtful. Watch the video, learn to identify cyberbullying, what to do in an uncomfortable situation, how to consider others' feelings, and how to be an upstander when cyberbullying occurs. Let's treat others as we would like to be treated. Printing is optional, complete the grade-appropriate Digital Media Sheet. Students, explore your favorite game site on the Internet for 20 min. Students take some time to practice being kind online. Most importantly, be safe and have fun!

Watch video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8rOnMl26dR8

post_text:
Hi Scholars!

Let's review the importance of your digital footprint. A digital footprint is a trail of data you create while using the Internet. It includes the websites you visit, emails you send, and the information you submit while online. Depending on how it is managed, this trail can be big or small, harmful, or helpful. Watch the video and take some time to reflect on your digital footprint. Printing is optional, complete the grade-appropriate Digital Media Sheet. Students, explore your favorite game site on the Internet for 20 min. Students compare the different trails you leave behind and think critically about what kinds of information you want to leave behind. Most importantly, be safe and have fun!

Watch video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7bRZdUtmH8k

Mrs. Boyer

Library Technology Specialist

Hi Scholars!

Let's take a moment and explore our feelings. Use your feelings to help you distinguish between good digital interaction and bad digital interaction. Let's make a point to be aware of our feelings even when we are on the internet. Remember, "when in doubt, talk it out". Anytime you are on the internet and something makes you feel uncomfortable, tell a trusted adult. Watch the video and take some time to reflect on your feelings. Printing is optional, complete the grade-appropriate Digital Media Sheet. Students, explore your favorite game site on the Internet for 20 min. Listen to your GUT, be more aware of your feelings, and tell a trusted adult if something doesn't make you feel comfortable when you use digital media. Most importantly, be safe and have fun!

Watch video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LB3nhKXm5E0

Best,

Mrs. Boyer

⚽️🏀🏈🏐🥏 PE Weekly Activities 🥏🏐🏈🏀⚽️
This week we will be working with the Spell It & Heads or Tails Challenges. Be sure to keep track of your work outs in your Activity Log to earn Oakside dollars.🤑

🔹Spell It - use the letters in names to guide you through the workout. (See pictures below) Example if I were spelling REDMAN my work out would start with R - 20 squats, then E- 20 squats, then D - 1 minute plank and so on.

🔹Heads or Tails- grab a coin. The coin decides what your work out is today.

🟠Monday: Spell It - Spell your full name & one other person’s name in the house.

🟡Tuesday: Heads or Tails - grab a coin. Play all 7 rounds

🟢Wednesday: Spell It- Spell your favorite teacher‘s name and your favorite book character‘s name for you workout.

🔵Thursday: Heads or Tails - grab a coin and a partner. You each take turns picking heads or tails. If you pick the right coin, the other person does the exercise. Play 2 rounds.

🟣Friday: Spell It - Spell the name of your favorite Movie and the word POPCORN. Then enjoy the weekend with your favorite movie & some popcorn 😜

post_text: I am so proud of the staff we have here at Oakside Scholars. We came together today to put a plan in place to make sure that learning continues throughout the school closure. The team has worked hard to create plans that will be easily accessible to you as parents, that will reinforce and maintain learning, and that will be engaging to students. Classdojo will be a key component in this plan. If you are not connected to Classdojo, we will be mailing out instructions for you access this app. Please do so as soon as you are able. I will send out more specific details in my weekly phone reach on Sunday. Please stay tuned to Classdojo for regular announcements. Our thoughts and prayers are with our community, state, and nation as we navigate through this time. Thank you for your continued partnership!

Oakside is joining The Great Kindness Challenge the week of Jan. 27- Jan. 31. A group of our middle school students (Culture Committee) are doing a fund raiser as part of the kindness challenge.
Following is a link for shirts they helped design. $4 of every shirt sold will go to WWF Australian Bush Fire Emergency Fund. The shirts will be delivered to Oakside Scholars on Jan. 31 for pick up.

https://www.jreshirts.com/oakside-elementary

The shirts on this site are only available for purchase until Monday January 27 at 12-noon. The vendor will disable the site at that time.
During that week, challenge yourself to do 10 acts of kindness a day. Post how many acts you did here on this thread. I want to see if together we can reach 5000 acts of kindness in 5 days. 🥰
Thank you for supporting our children in building a culture of kindness and compassion.
Check out thegreatkindnesschallenge.com or download The Great Kindness Challenge app in your app store, available for ios.
